# 📚 Smart Library Management System (Console-Based in Java)

A modular Java application simulating a **microservices-like structure** for managing library operations including book borrowing, returns, user registration, and admin book management. Built using **Core Java**, **OOP principles**, and **file-based storage** — no database or REST APIs required.

---

## 🚀 Features

- 👤 User Registration & Login
- 📖 View, Borrow, and Return Books
- 🔐 Admin Panel to Add Books & View Transactions
- 📁 Persistent Storage using `.dat` files (Java Serialization)
- 🔄 Simulated Microservice Structure using Java Classes
- 🧾 Console-based user interface

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Component        | Technology         |
|------------------|--------------------|
| Language         | Java (Core Java)   |
| Storage          | Java File I/O (.dat files) |
| Design Pattern   | OOP + Modular Classes |
| UI               | Console            |

---

## 📂 Folder Structure

```bash
SmartLibrarySystem.java        # Main program file
books.dat                      # Book data (auto-created)
users.dat                      # Registered users
transactions.dat               # Borrow/Return history
